What the hell is DFView?
========================

`DFView' is *not* just a viewer. It is a bit less and a bit more than
this.

`DFView' allows you to handle file lists in quite a comfortable way. It
allows you to configure an *external* program. `DFView' processes the
files within the filelist and processes them calling the external
program.

`DFView' was programmed using `MUI' ((C) Stefan Stuntz). This means
1st. that you need `MUI' to run this program!  As `MUI' needs at least
*AMIGA*OS V2.04 (V37.175), you must have this OS installed!

`DFView' is using `MUI'.  You not only get an application icon, the
typical 2.0 look and feel but better, you can do all operations by
keyboard!  `DFView' is a commodity, so you can pop it up by holding
down the "hotkey".  There is LOCALE-Support as well.  Notice that you
*need* *AMIGA*OS V2.1 or V3.0 (or even better) to take advantage of
this feature.  If you are still using V2.0x, `DFView' takes the english
texts.


@EndNode

@Node "History" "DFView.guide/History"
@Prev "What the hell is DFView?"
@Toc "General"

History
=======

In spring 1993 I got to know the MagicUserInterface ((C) 1993, Stefan
Stuntz). I liked it at once and soon time after I decided to program a
"little" tool to learn how `MUI' works (learning by doing).

The weeks and months have passed and the "little" tool `DFView' became
bigger and bigger. I tried to implement as many features (e.g.  Locale
support) as possible, to see if `MUI' is suitable for larger projects
as well. And voila - I think, `DFView' became quite a useful piece of
software.


@EndNode

