Installation
************

   *  Please install `MUI' to your harddisk. `DFView' does *not* work
     without `MUI'.

   *  Copy the `DFView' executable and its `.info' file to a drawer in
     your search path. If you copy it to the `WBStartup' drawer, it
     will be started automatically during booting.

   *  Copy the catalog file(s) (locale/<language>/DFView.catalog) to
     Locale:Catalogs/<language>. Please notice that you get locale
     support only, if you already upgraded to Workbench 2.1 or above.

   *  Copy the documentation files (`DFView.dvi', `DFView.guide',
     `DFView.doc') to any destination that suits your needs. Please
     notice that the `DFView.guide' has to be in the proper drawer to
     be found by `MUI's online help system. Please read the `MUI'
     documentation for details.

Well - that's it.  Now you can use either the shell to start `DFView'
manually by typing `DFView' or `run DFView >NIL: <NIL:', or you double
click on it from the Workbench.

As mentioned above, if you copied `DFView' to the `WBStartup' drawer it
will start automatically while booting.


@EndNode

