Files
=====

Using the `Files' listview and the attached buttons you can completely
manage the filelist.

   * *Add*

     If you hit `Add', a filerequester pops up and you may select one
     or more files for the file list. After you finished the selection
     the file(s) is/are shown in the listview.

   * *Remove*

     Removes the active item.

   * *Rem. sel.*

     Removes all currently selected items.

   * *Sort*

     Sorts the items.

   * *All*

     Selects all items currently available.

   * *Toggle*

     Changes the select state of all items in the listview, i.e. all
     selected items become deselected an vice versa.

   * *Pattern*

     If you hit this button, another (small) window pops up and you may
     enter a select pattern. All entries in the listview that fit the
     pattern will be selected.

   * *None*

     All entries become deselected.

   * *Top*

     The currently active item becomes the first one.

   * *Up*

     The currently active item is moved one line up.

   * *Down*

     The currently active item is moved one line down.

   * *Bottom*

     The currently active item becomes the last one.


@EndNode

@Node "File list" "DFView.guide/File list"
@Next "Quick change"
@Prev "Files"
@Toc "DFView Step by Step"

File list
=========

   * *Clear*

     Clears the listview (Removes all entries). The file preferences
     are *not* cleared!

   * *Load*

     Loads a filelist.

   * *Save*

     Saves a filelist.

   * *Prefs*

     The file preferences window gives you the possibility to adjust
     some parameters for *every* file list. These parameters are saved
     together with the filelist itself. See @{"File Preferences" Link "FPrefs"} for
     details.


