Process
-------

There exist three kinds of processing the *selected* files. They can be
processed `one by one', which means that the command (see above) is
called for *every* selected file. Only this file is given to the
command.

If you select `all at once', all selected items in the file list are
given to the command. If there are more files selected than the
internal limit allows, only as many files are processed as are
possible. The other files are *not* used.

`All until done' tries to give you a workaround for the internal
command size limit mentioned above. It processes as many commands as
possible. When processing these files is finished, it continues with
the remaining.


@EndNode

